# Cognitive Intelligence Evolution (Built-in SLM)

Implement a local, built-in AI "brain" to enhance agent reasoning with minimal resource usage.

## ⚠️ Requirements & Dependencies

- **Storage**: ~1GB for the specialized model.
- **Dependencies**: `llama-cpp-python` (built-in inference), `huggingface_hub` (model management).

## Proposed Changes

### [Core Engine]

#### [NEW] [cognitive_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/utils/cognitive_engine.py)

- Single entry point for local inference.
- Handles model download and caching logic.
- Implements context management for the SLM.

#### [MODIFY] [base.py](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/agents/base.py)

- Add `self.cognitive_core` to [BaseActivePersona](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/agents/base.py#9-104).
- Implement a [reason()](file:///c:/Users/joaovitormagdaleno/Documents/GitHub/Personas_Agentes/src_local/agents/Python/flow.py#26-37) helper method to facilitate AI calls from specialists.

### [Persona Agents]

#### [NEW] [TestRefiner] [Refactor Specialist]

- Prototypes for agents that use the AI brain to generate code or explain complex logic.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `pytest tests/test_cognitive_core.py` (Mocked vs Real mode).
